details.description:
This post card shows a picture of a Church in Aden where Gunner Daniel Davies was based in 1914/15. He has written a note on the back saying that this was the Church he goes to every Sunday. The inscription on the back of this postcard from Daniel Davies which says&nbsp;&lsquo;This is the Church I go to every Sunday.&rsquo;
&nbsp;
It should be noted that a memorial plaque was placed in the church in&nbsp; 1916 which said&nbsp;&ldquo;In Memory of the following N.C.Os & Men of the Breconshire Battalion South Wales Borderers who died while on Active Service at Aden 1914-15.&quot;
&nbsp;
This plaque&nbsp;was moved some time after WW2 to Brecon Cathedral, but has subsequently been lost.&nbsp;
